USE MINTDB;

GO
CHECKPOINT;
DBCC SHRINKFILE (MINTDB_log, 1024);

GO
DBCC SHRINKDATABASE(N'MINTDB', 10, TRUNCATEONLY);





Common Mistake: Log File Not Shrinking
People often try to shrink a log file, but it doesnâ€™t work if:

No log backups exist
Recovery model is FULL but no backups are being taken

Solution:
Do a full backup
Then do a log backup
Then you can shrink
